My main focus with coaching is truly helping people and Paying it Forward.  I have a passion for helping people maximize their life through health and fitness!! But the fact that I am able to work from home, helping people get healthy and fit is still so crazy to me!!! Seriously! --- I thought that being a personal trainer was my ideal job in life but I realized that I was working around other people's hours and as rewarding and gratifying as it was, working early morning's and after work hours started to really ware on me.  It took me away from my husband and once we had kids, from them! 
This opportunity was presented to me and to be honest, I totally pre-judged it and said No Way! But once I researched it, I took a chance and little by little I fell in love! 
Fell in love with that feeling of being able to help people, in love with "working" when I chose to (not other people), in love with the products and company and what they stood for, in love for helping other people (through the coaching opportunity) to live their life by design! The no hormone claim doesn't mean much because federal law already prohibits hormone use in all #poultry and pork, but what matters is there are no antibiotics, no cannibalism (yes, traditional, non-organic chickens are fed chicken...not only is that gross but it is well documented that cannibalism causes disease. Yum?) Organic chickens are also spared from having their beaks cut off (no anesthesia!) and grow at normal rates (traditional chickens grow too much and so fast--with all the antibiotics pumped into them-- and as a result many get sores on their skin and pus, and many times their legs cannot hold their weight. It is not uncommon to find many wallowing in their own waste...yum?). #noAntibiotics #organicCooking #organicChicken #organicMeat #antibioticFree #flexitarian #flexitarianism #semivegetarianism"

Comment: keniawriter said "Sunday (m)eats! I'm a meat-once-a-week #semivegetarian, and for this week I was craving my mom's homemade #hotWings. I picked up #organic wings from #wholeFoods. The no hormone claim doesn't mean much because federal law already prohibits hormone use in all #poultry and pork, but what matters is there are no antibiotics, no cannibalism (yes, traditional, non-organic chickens are fed chicken...not only is that gross but it is well documented that cannibalism causes disease. Yum?) Organic chickens are also spared from having their beaks cut off (no anesthesia!) and grow at normal rates (traditional chickens grow too much and so fast--with all the antibiotics pumped into them-- and as a result many get bloody sores on their skin and pus, and many times their legs cannot hold their unnatural weight. It is not uncommon to find many wallowing in their own waste...yum?). #noAntibiotics #organicCooking #organicChicken #organicMeat #antibioticFree #flexitarian #flexitarianism #semivegetarianism #feedYourBody"

Comment: ed.templeton said "#dailyHBpiervideo - As social media and cell phones buzzed the news to people what would have been a normal lazy Monday in #huntingtonbeach turned into a frenzy of happy people flocking to the beach and pier to see that inch of hail that cloaked the sand and downtown in a white blanket. This is the 3rd time in my 40+ year life that snow/hail actually stayed on the ground for any length of time in HB. People were frolicking, shooting photos, making and throwing snowballs, doing snow angels, building small icy showmen, one guy took off his shirt and did a belly slide down the slope of ice on the grass, the little shards of ice shredding his stomach, bad choice. Then the sun came out around 12:00 and started scorching as usual and within the hour the little balls of ice were absorbed back into the earth. The people from everywhere else in the U.S. shook their heads at us with disdain. But for us it was a rare treat to see our normally sun kissed beach covered in winter white, if only shortly, and then quickly morph back to bikini weather. #surfcityusa #snowinHB #hailinHB"

Comment: dj_oldboy said "On Saturday, there was this #clevergirl who kept writing mr request notes. I loved these for many reasons. One-they were multiple choice notes. She didnt drunkenly yell at me or bother me, she just quietly slipped me these notes, and I could acknowledge them at my leisure between tambo dances. Two-the requests! They are so amazingly ridiculous. I love how she confused Hoop Dreams mans Hang Time. Tho, Hang Time and Hoop Dreams were both high school related, not college. Both are so completely different. But, ever so appreciated. . And I omg I wish I had anything Saved By The Bell related on vinyl! Upside down is a request for Mary Poppins. This is all shit I would nerd out on in my room like some geeked out scientist. Mashing up weird, wild stuff. 
I love my nights at the Pike. I never know what's gonna happen. I'm so relieved and thankful when playful, innocent, funny, arbitrary things happen. What's interesting, is that this is sorta my goal. To open up this world. I want my night to be a crazy, geeky, entertaining house party.

The officer is currently standing trial at a Louisiana court and has been charged with one count of negligent homicide. The homeless man killed by LeDoux was later identified as Raymond Keith Martinez. The incident happened in early December on the store located on 7th Street in West Monroe.

Comment: punkabillyturk said "49,933. This is the number of homeless on any given night that are veterans. Of that about 12,700 are from Operation Enduring Freedom, Operation Iraqi Freedom and Operation New Dawn. Why you ask? Shortage of affordable housing, livable income and access to health care along with the effects of PTSD and substance abuse. veterans helping veterans seems to work the best but that doesn't meant you can't help. Reach out to a vet, any vet. You never know just how close one is to being homeless. Participate in local community homeless events. Do anything! Do something! #ThankAVeteranThursday #TAVT #veteran #vets4vets #homeless #homelessveterans #EndTheCycle"

Comment: coachsallyg said "CHEW YOUR FOOD!

This is going to help make my body get ready for my fitness shoot this weekend. But not just the meal plan, I intend to chew my food!! Mindful eating is rarely practiced and every time I eat out I feel the need to do a presentation on how to eat and chew properly. It's such a simple (but not commonly practiced) health habit than can make a huge difference in how you look and feel. 
Mahatma Gandhi said after reviewing lots of scientific information "Chew your drink and DRINK your food". What wise words to live by. 
______________________________

Put your fork, spoon or chopsticks down between each bite and chew until the food is liquified. A good rule to follow is 30-50 chews per small bite. Make sure you swallow completely before putting more food in your mouth. 
______________________________

Would you like guidance on what to eat, when to eat, and how to put all your meals together? Tell me ğŸ˜˜"

Mindful eating is rarely practiced and every time I eat out I feel the need to do a presentation on how to eat and chew properly. Comment: meleesathesalon said "-----------HOW---TO--------------
Adorable easy headband updo
1. Place headband over hair, leaving the ends to hang down underneath
2. Starting in the front, section out a small piece of hair
3. Tuck the hair around the headband
4. Continue working your way around the head, tucking pieces around the band
5. Secure the remainder of the hanging hair, pinning if needed
6. Enjoy your easy updo! -----------------------------------------------------------
#updo #headband #easyupdo #howto #tutorial #hair #hairstyles #purplehair #MTShowto #meleesathesalon #huntingtonbeach #hb #hbbraidbar #ocorangecounty #hairbywendi"

Comment: cacareercafe said "Develop 3 questions to ask during the interview. 
Most interviews end with the question â€œDo you have any questions for me?â€ The worst thing you can do is say no. You should always have some questions prepared in advance. 
Although it might not feel like it, an interview is really a two-way street. You are permitted-- in fact, expected-- to ask questions and engage in the conversation. 
The types of questions you ask will be importantâ€”they can reveal how much research youâ€™ve already done. So you donâ€™t want to ask things like the salary for the position (that will come in a later discussion after the job offer) or ask questions which could have been easily answered by reading the website. 
Ask questions related to the job or the organization, such as: 
I read an article that said you were considering expanding your business to the west coast. Is that still a possibility? 
How would you describe the work style in the division where I might be working? 
Who succeeds in this position? (Always link your personality traits with the ones described.) How much guidance or assistance is provided during my first year of employment? 
Develop 3 questions you can ask at the interview. Make sure you are genuinely interested in the answers and analyze them for what they might reveal about you.  #interview #questions #dreamjob #internship"

Comment: calcoastsc_hb said "Taking advantage of an active recovery day to introduce the group to pacing. 15 rounds of 30 seconds work on a ski erg, 90 seconds full rest. .

It's important to maintain mental focus throughout a workout. Working on pacing and hitting a target distance each round on an erg helps ingrain that focus. This workout is usually done by increasing one meter each round and performing an exercise during the "rest", but we built it into a recovery day and worked to hit the same target each round. It served its purpose well. .

#CalCoastHB #GymJones #HuntingtonBeach #California"

Comment: calcoastsc_hb said "Taking advantage of an active recovery day to introduce the group to pacing. 15 rounds of 30 seconds work on a ski erg, 90 seconds full rest. .

It's important to maintain mental focus throughout a workout. Working on pacing and hitting a target distance each round on an erg helps ingrain that focus. This workout is usually done by increasing one meter each round and performing an exercise during the "rest", but we built it into a recovery day and worked to hit the same target each round. It served its purpose well. .

Healthy Homemade Granola
3 cups of rolled oats
1 cup mixed nuts&seeds 
1/2 cup shredded coconut
1/4 teaspoon ground cinnamon
1cup agave nectar
1cup dried fruit

Oven 350. 
Mix all ingredients (except dried fruit) and spread evenly on a rimmed baking sheet.
Bake 30 minutes (stir every 5-10 minutes to make sure it doesn't burn)

But I honestly could not be happier that the last thing he said to me was "I love you son". I will cherish that moment forever, and no one can take that away from me. 
Thank you to everyone who has called, texted, or talked to me in person these last 33 hours. Thank you for everything, I love you all."

Comment: jessicaquillian said "About #12weeksout from the @spectrumfitnessproductions #norcal show and I'm still reverse dieting. Haven't started carb cycling or cutting yet. I must admit that I've had a tough time in the off season and have messed up on my reverse dieting a few times. I'm human though and I make mistakes and my diet isn't always 100% perfect and that's ok. I am constantly improving and learning from my mistakes, which I believe molds me into a stronger person and an even better coach and competitor. When my clients go through the ups and downs that are bound to happen with competing, I've been there and I'm able to relate and understand what they're going through. And I must say that my coach @jamidebernard is amazing and is so supportive of me. She's never condescending or blameful if I slip up; she's encouraging and lifts me back up when I'm having a bad moment. And I've had coaches who have been very condescending and pretty hurtful when I've slipped up and that's not ok in my book. So thanks to @jamidebernard for making this journey so positive for me! Comment: aftannfit said "Chocolate Chip + Banana + Oatmeal Bites 
Ingredients
-2 very ripe #bananas, mashed -1 cup oats, rolled or quick -1/2 teaspoon cinnamon
-small handful semi-sweet chocolate chips or cacao nibs

Optional add-ins:
dash of vanilla extract
shredded coconut
chopped nuts
dried fruit
a few tablespoons nut butter

Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. 
In a medium size bowl, mash bananas fairly smooth, a few small chunks is ok. Add oats and cinnamon, mix well. Add in chocolate chips, mix again.

Grease a cookie sheet. Using a tablespoon, scoop mixture and place on cookie sheet. Should get anywhere from 12 -16 depending on the size you scoop.

Bake in oven for 15 - 25 minutes depending on the size of your cookie. #aftannFIT #healthycookies"

Comment: aftannfit said "Chocolate Chip + Banana + Oatmeal Bites 
Ingredients
-2 very ripe #bananas, mashed -1 cup oats, rolled or quick -1/2 teaspoon cinnamon
-small handful semi-sweet chocolate chips or cacao nibs

Optional add-ins:
dash of vanilla extract
shredded coconut
chopped nuts
dried fruit
a few tablespoons nut butter

Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. 
In a medium size bowl, mash bananas fairly smooth, a few small chunks is ok. Add oats and cinnamon, mix well. Add in chocolate chips, mix again.

Grease a cookie sheet. Using a tablespoon, scoop mixture and place on cookie sheet. Should get anywhere from 12 -16 depending on the size you scoop.

Bake in oven for 15 - 25 minutes depending on the size of your cookie. #aftannFIT #healthycookies"

Comment: aftannfit said "Chocolate Chip + Banana + Oatmeal Bites 
Ingredients
-2 very ripe #bananas, mashed -1 cup oats, rolled or quick -1/2 teaspoon cinnamon
-small handful semi-sweet chocolate chips or cacao nibs

Optional add-ins:
dash of vanilla extract
shredded coconut
chopped nuts
dried fruit
a few tablespoons nut butter

Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. 
In a medium size bowl, mash bananas fairly smooth, a few small chunks is ok. Add oats and cinnamon, mix well. Add in chocolate chips, mix again.

Grease a cookie sheet. Using a tablespoon, scoop mixture and place on cookie sheet. Should get anywhere from 12 -16 depending on the size you scoop.

Bake in oven for 15 - 25 minutes depending on the size of your cookie. #aftannFIT #healthycookies"

Comment: aftannfit said "Chocolate Chip + Banana + Oatmeal Bites 
Ingredients
-2 very ripe #bananas, mashed -1 cup oats, rolled or quick -1/2 teaspoon cinnamon
-small handful semi-sweet chocolate chips or cacao nibs

Optional add-ins:
dash of vanilla extract
shredded coconut
chopped nuts
dried fruit
a few tablespoons nut butter

Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. 
In a medium size bowl, mash bananas fairly smooth, a few small chunks is ok. Add oats and cinnamon, mix well. Add in chocolate chips, mix again.

Grease a cookie sheet. Using a tablespoon, scoop mixture and place on cookie sheet. Should get anywhere from 12 -16 depending on the size you scoop.

Bake in oven for 15 - 25 minutes depending on the size of your cookie. #aftannFIT #healthycookies"

Comment: velascarves said "VELA'S 1ST #HIJABIFIED GIRL @leenasalah in her black cotton modal scarf provided by @velascarves:

Leenah: "Hello everyone! My name is Leena and I am 20 years old! As a new Hijabi, I have experience both the good and the bad. The good being that my family and friends have been so supportive of my decision. And the bad being the ignorant comments and looks I get from some people. In all honesty these ignorant remarks have made me such a stronger person and has helped encourage me grow and embrace the beautiful head piece. I was motivated to take that next step to wear hijab because of how I see my lovely mother carry herself with pride each time she steps foot outside of our house. For the past couple of years I would go to Islamic events and conventions and there I would learn more and more about islam. Knowing that I wear the hijab and please Allah the all mighty is the best feeling ever! 
Advice I would give to anyone who is considering wearing hijab and might be struggling would be to talk to someone you look up to, someone you know you could trust and more importantly someone who has faith in Allah and embraces the religion of Islam. You want to be able to relate to that person because at one point in life, they probably struggled with hijab as well and they would know exactly what you might be going through. Alhamdulilah, I am surrounded by amazing people who gave me amazing advice and have helped make the tradition easier. I hope and pray that who ever is thinking of wearing hijab has a smooth transition inshAllah. Hijab is a beautiful thing!" #hijabified"
